The municipal administration, provincial administration or the General Assembly can consider the exclusion or suspension (5.1. d.) of a member by a two-thirds majority, because it is not possible to do so:
a. he/she is acting contrary to the articles of association, regulations or of the statutory party bodies and/or because;
b. he/she unreasonably prejudices the party by not fulfilling his/her obligations towards the party or by acting contrary to them. The decision to consider a suspension or exclusion shall be immediately communicated to the member concerned by registered letter, stating the reasons. A copy of this letter shall be sent to the higher and/or lower boards as well as to the general secretariat.

