A member of the party is obliged to
- follow the statutes and fulfil the decisions of the party executive bodies;
- pay membership dues [...];
- if elected, participate actively in the executive bodies of the party;
- not to damage the reputation of the party and help to raise party reputation;
- not to participate in the work of any group, association or organization, the activities or goals of which are contradictory to the programmatic positions of the party.
